gPrNQM1l5fMZwFPsbRbcXwDin17h2KOB0OiOoF87znviqDnxWw\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking system status**\\n\\nI don't think I need any files or memory today; maybe just focusing on what's necessary for March 24, 2026. I need to respond to the watchdog check, which probably expects a HEARTBEAT_OK because it's night and things seem normal. But I wonder if I should double-check the watchdog? The cron message indicates to avoid disturbance unless something's abnormal, so I’m leaning towards saying HEARTBEAT_OK. Let's keep it minimal!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_088101eff6a565200169c2bcbeec148191b095002d8a041859\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1993,"output":86,"cacheRead":13696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15775,"cost":{"input":0.004982500000000001,"output":0.0012900000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003424,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0096965}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774369977329,"responseId":"resp_088101eff6a565200169c2bcb9d52c819180c6780b02a7b5fc"}}
